<html>
<head>
<title>
Welfare Survey Results
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">
<h2><center>Welfare Survey Results</center></h2>
<hr>
<b>Question:</b> Do you believe "Welfare Reform" is an important for Congress to address?<P>
Yes: 100%<br>
No: 0%<P>

<b>Question:</b> Do you believe the Republicans or the Democrats are more sincere about reforming welfare?<P>

Republicans: 98%<br>
Democrats: 2%<p>

<b>Question</b> Under the current system, those on welfare are able to remain with the system for an indefinite period of time. Should welfare reform include a "2 year and your're out" clause?<P>

Yes: 91:<br>
No: 9%<p>

<b>Question</b> The House version of welfare reform included a "family cap" that would cap payments to welfare mothers that have additional children. The Senate deleted this from it's version.  Do you support the "family cap"?<p>

Yes: 91%<br>
No: 9%<P>

<b>Question</b> In the final version of welfare reform that comes out of the conference committee doesn't contain provisions such as the "family cap", or AFDC limits to un-wed teenagers, how should the conservative freshmen who have fought for these provisions, vote on the final bill?<P>

Yes: 50%<br>
No: 50%<p>

<b>Question</b> If Welfare reform does not pass this year, who will you hold responsible?<P>

Republicans: 48%<br>
Democrats: 52%<p>

</body>
</html>
</DOC>
