<TITLE>Washington Watch: The Newsletter</TITLE>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000">

<center>
<table border=6>
<tr><td>
<IMG SRC="/townhall/FRC/wwatch/wwatch.gif">
</td></tr>
</table>
<p></center>
<b><i>Washington Watch</i></b> is a four-page newsletter  tailored to the needs of busy households and work places.  Published 10 times a year, <b><i>Watch</i></b> monitors developments in Congress, the courts, and the White House that affect families' daily lives.  Besides offering strong reportage, <b><i>Watch</i></b> evaluates vital legislative and regulatory actions, discussing their impact on <I> your </I>family, and advising you where to write to communicate the pro-family position or point of view.
<P>
The most recent issues of <b><i>Washington Watch</i></b> are listed below.  Other 
issues will be made available shortly for your convenience.
<UL>
<LI><A HREF = "/townhall/FRC/wwatch/ww95f.html">June 1995</A>
